large lags¶

Its pretty clear that the CTD and pressure sensor are quite offset in time from one another.

In [77]:
with xr.open_dataset('L1-timeseries/rosie713-20190314T1920_L1.nc', decode_times=False) as ds:
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 3, sharey=True)
    for n, k in enumerate(['temperature', 'conductivity', 'oxygen_concentration']):
        ax = axs[n]

The lag between temperature and pressure appears to be about 26 seconds with the CTD lagging the pressure sensor.

In [78]:
with xr.open_dataset('L1-timeseries/rosie713-20190314T1920_L1.nc', decode_times=False) as ds:
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 3, sharey=True)
    lags = [26, 21, 29]
    for n, k in enumerate(['temperature', 'conductivity', 'oxygen_concentration']):
        ax = axs[n]
        lag = lags[n]

        pc = ax.plot( ds[k], ds.depth, '.', markersize=1)
        ax.set_ylim([140, 0])
        ax.set_xlabel(ds[k].attrs['long_name'])
        if n == 0:
            ax.set_ylabel('Depth [m]')
           
        dt = - np.median(ds.time.values[:-lag] - ds.time.values[lag:])
        ax.set_title(f'lag={lag} samples;\n{dt:1.3f} s', fontsize=9)
        pc = ax.plot(ds[k][lag:], ds.depth[:-lag], '.', markersize=1)

In [79]:
with xr.open_mfdataset('rawnc/*.ebd.nc', decode_times=False) as ds:
    lag = 10
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot( ds.sci_water_cond, ds.sci_water_pressure * 10, '.', markersize=1)    
    good = np.where(~np.isnan(ds.sci_water_pressure * 10 + ds.sci_water_cond))
    ax.plot(ds.sci_water_cond[good][lag:], ds.sci_water_pressure[good][:-lag] * 10,  '.', markersize=1)
    ax.set_ylim([120, 0])
    ax.set_xlim([3., 3.43])
    ax.set_ylabel('P [dbar]')
    ax.set_xlabel('C [S/m]')
